genresAdvancedInfo.name: santa fe indie
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Santa Fe Indie is a sub-genre of indie rock that originated in Santa Fe, New Mexico. It is characterized by its eclectic mix of folk, country, and rock influences, as well as its emphasis on introspective lyrics and DIY production values. The sound is often characterized by acoustic guitar, mandolin, and other traditional instruments, as well as lo-fi recording techniques that give the music a raw, organic feel.
